"Criminy! Quit shovin', ya crumbum!" you snarl as rough hands push your forward.  You topple head over heels, but expertly parlay your fall into a somersault, landing lightly on your heels and knuckles. Yup, no sweat.  You don't get to be a big time public enemy -- or even just a surviving street urchin -- without being quick on your toes.

Because, of course, that's what you are: A street urchin.  And not just any street urchin.  You're Lil' Ragamuffin, the roughest, toughest street urchin to ever roam the backalleys of Depression-era Garbagetown DC. A real nail-spittin', rail-splittin' little hellfire imp and nobody's sweetheart.

"Don't be gettin' wise wit' us, kid," growls the owner of the hands.  He's a big meaty slab of a man, stuffed into an ill-fitting pinstriped suit, compulsively cracking his big hairy knuckles as if you dare you to make a move.  He's flanked by two even bigger, meatier guys.

"You shoulda known betta than to go troo da garbage cans a' the Macaroni Family," says the main meaty goon. He cracks his knuckles again, just to remind you that he has them. "We been lookin' fer th' lil' scamp dats been eatin' our leavin's fer weeks now, an' if'n ya knew whut was good fer yous, ya woulda left well enough alone! What're ya lookin' fer in dere, kid? Some old whiskey bottles as evidence against us? You on da coppers' payroll?"

You spit. "Blow it out yer ear, screw! Lil' Ragamuffin don't work for no cop!"

"Says you! We can't take no chance. So we's gonna leave ya in here ta think about what ya done. At least untils da boss decides what he wants ta do wit' ya.  Can't have no kid detective spillin' da beans to da coppers 'bout our lil' speakeasy-- I mean, our legitimate business operation here!"

"Dat's right, Tony," rumbles the goon to Tony's right. "We don't sell no al-kee-hol here, right? Jest nice legal sody water!"

The goons share a hearty laugh over what apparently passes for a joke amongst mafia goons.

Gadzooks! All you were doing was eating some old shoes out of the trashcans, as a street urchin is wont to do, but it seems like these mobsters really think you were after some dirt on them! Well, that don't matter none; it's not like they can keep you here.

"Better put an extra lock on th' door, ya mooks!" you shout, picking yourself up and dusting yourself off. "There ain't a hoosegow or a waif tank built that can hold th' like a' Lil' Ragamuffin! I'll be out in two shakes of a lamb's tail, I will!"

"Yeah, we taught you'd say dat," says Tony, a cruel sneer curling his lips. "Dat's why we took da liberty of seperatin' ya from her lil' rat friend!"

Your blood instantly runs cold. For the first time, you realize how light your shoulder feels.  Percy, you best friend and ever-present sewer rat companion, ALWAYS rides on your shoulder.

"You freakin' scallawags!" you shout, "What're ya done wit' Percy?! If'n ya harmed one hair on his lil' ratty head, I'll--"

"'Eeeeey, relax, sweetheart!" chuckles Tony, "Yer pal is fine fer now. We just got him locked up fer safe keepin'. 'Course, can't say how long he'll be keepin' safe.  A nice big rat like him, boy, I bet he'd be quite a draw down at da rattin' pit. Might even last a whole round or two against Jocko."

"Jocko!? Who the aich ee double hockey sticks is Jocko?" you snarl.

"Oh yeah, da champ. Jocko is only the finest fightin' ferret ta ever brawl in the' rattin' pit of the Baleful Backwash Casino & Speakeasy! I wouldn't bet much on yer pal lastin' da night. Haha!"

"You ain't gonna get away wit' this!" you shout as Tony and his chuckling goons step out of the room, slamming the door shut behind them.  You hear a key jangle in the lock and the heavy-duty mechanism snap closed with a sickening click. "I'll bust outta here! An' rescue Percy! Just you wait an' see! Or my name ain't Lil' Ragamuffin... which it is!"

You gnash your teeth angrily as you listen to the goons' raucous laughter recede into the distance, but you don't have time to dwell on your plight.  You need to get out of here... and recuse Percy... and fast!

You are in a wine cellar.
You can see barrels, a keg and a still.
You can go north.
You are in a dank and dark basement room, a single incandescent lightbulb swinging overhead provides the only light. The walls are little more than packed earth, lined with wooden barrels of illicit moonshine. There's a still in the corner, emitting steady bubbling and gurgling noises as it does its thirsty work.

The only exit would be the door to the north, but it's locked.

[First time playing a Quest game? Type 'help' anytime for some pointers about playing a Quest game.]
> x me

> x me
It's you, Lil' Ragamuffin -- the roughest, toughest urchin to ever scuttle the backalleys and gutters of Garbagetown DC and the best apple snatcher east of the Allegheny Plateau ! Rags to your friends, but, according to the wanted posters issued by the Office of the Urchinfinder General, also known as Red Rags, Black Ashes, Kid Pilliwinks, The Firebrat, God’s Murder, The Corpse Maker, and, in the northwestern territories, The Bane of Queen Molly.
