> x still
The still consists of several large copper chambers, linked by a tangle of pipes and tubes, through which amber liquid flows. The whole contraption bubbles and burbles angrily, working hard to distill corn mash into something that won't kill you but will probably make you wish that it did. The fumes coming off the still are so strong that you feel woozy just being in the same room with it.
