> push keg

> push keg
You shove your shoulder against the keg until it begins to move, slowly building up momentum until it crashes into the wall and smashes to splinters, spilling moonshine all over the floor. You notice that there is a mousehole chewed into the wall, until now obscured by the keg.
> x mousehole

> x mousehole
An eager mouse has chewed a hole into the wall.
> look in it

> look in it
You get down on your hands and knees and peer into the mousehole.  It's full of snips and scraps, the sort of things a packrat would collect, but one thing catches your eye: a matchbook.
> x matchbook

> x matchbook
A small wooden box, small enough to fit into the palm of your hand, full of matches.
> take it

> take it
You reach into the hole and grab the matchbook with your fingers.
> use rope on still

> use rope on still
Holding your breath, you gingerly shove one end of the rope into the open top of the still's exit chamber, soaking it in high-concentrate alcohol, then unfurl the rope across the rope.  Now hopefully it'll serve as a makeshift fuse.
> light fuse

> light fuse
You strike a match against the ground, then hold it to the hemp fuse until it starts to smolder.  You scamper away to hide behind the barrels as the spark travels quickly up the rope and into the still and...

KABOOOOM!!!

You're nearly thrown into the wall as the still explodes into shaprel, spraying half-finished moonshine all over the room.  The noise leaves a ringing in your ears, but, when the dust clears, you see that you've successfully blown the cell door of its hinges. Alright! Now to find Percy...
