"Oy! So, how's th' bum life treatin' ya?" you ask jovially. As an urchin, you, of course, feel a natural kinship with all your fellow wanderers, be they hoodlum, hobo, delinquent, or bum.

"S'great!" says Murray the bum, taking another swig from his bottle. "Ya do whatever ya want, whenever ya want! No schedules, no obligations! Nothin' ta do but nothin'! An' nothin' ta worry 'bout but me an' my lil' ol' bottle here!"
> ask Murray about bottle

> ask Murray about bottle
"Aw, you talkin' bout this lil' ol' bottle right here?" says Murray the bum, clutching his bottle to his face. "This bottle's jest about my best friend in the whole wide world! Who can make ya ferget your troubles faster than a nice bottle a' sweet coffin varnish?"

"Oy, you makes it sound pretty nice," you say, "Mind'n if I took a slug?"

"Buzz off, kid!" snaps Murray the bum. "This here bottle belongs ta me!"
> ask Murray about barrels

> ask Murray about barrels
"Oh, what barrels? I soitenly don't know nothin' bout no empty barrels! Hic!"
> ask Murray about Percy

> ask Murray about Percy
"Oy, Murray the bum, I'm tryin' ta bust my pal outta the hoosegow. Got any suggestions?"

Murray the bum shrugs. "I don't got no ideas now, but ask me in another few bottles. I always do my best thinkin' after a couple drinks!"
> ask Murray about Tony

> ask Murray about Tony
"Oy, Murray the bum, ain't ya scared of them gangsters? If'n they find ya down here, drinkin' their hooch, they's liable to be mighty sore! And them fellers look like they play fer keeps!"

Murray waves his hand dismissively. "Aw, applesauce! Them creeps can't keep a good bum down! What a buncha maroons, thinkin' they could hide all this hooch down here an' I wouldn't find it? What were they smokin', eh? Hic!"

You scratch your head. "Oy, jest a tic, Murray the bum, how DID ya get down here?"

"Funny story!" says Murray the bum. "I was up at Luigi Tang's Happy Jade Panda Bottega, tryin' ta hawk some of me old army medals so'n I could buy me a hit of Jamaican Jake, when I jest fell right through a trapdoor into this heaven! Now I got all the hooch I could ever want! Hic!"
> ask Murray about army

> ask Murray about army
"So, you was in the army?" you say, "Wot was that like? You kill anyone?"

"Yeah, I was over'in French Verdun back in th' Great War! Kept the Kaiser from bitin' the heads offa kittens all by myself! Glad ta be outta the army, though, can't stand all them drill sergents always yellin'. 'Course I still can't help if'n I still get stirred to attention by that damn military music."
> ask Murray about music

> ask Murray about music
"I can't stand them military marches," snorts Murray the bum. "I hear 'em and I just about lose my cotton-pickin' mind! They put me back in mind o' boot camp an' I just can't stop myself: I just get up an' march!"
