"Just a friendly game of poker!" chirps Skunkface Sally in a nasal Brooklyn accent. "I just love a good poker game, eh? Too bad that I'm so bad at it that I always lose, eh? Eh? Golly, if we could only get a fourth for the game, I bet they'd totally clean up since we're all soooo bad at poker!"
> ask Sally about Jimmy

> ask Sally about Jimmy
"He's a good goon," says Skunkface Sally. "Ain't no one who can bust kneecaps better than Jimmy the Weasel. But he can't play poker worth a plug cent."

"Awww, applesauce," snorts Jimmy the Weasel.
> ask Sally about Mulligan

> ask Sally about Mulligan
"Don't let that ugly mug fool ya, kid," says Skunkface Sally, playfully mussing her surly companion's hair. "He's just a big ol' kitten deep down."

Two-Eyed Mulligan doesn't change expression. He just continues to glare. Yeah. A real kitten.
> ask Sally about Tony

> ask Sally about Tony
"Tony is da boss's kid," says Skunkface Sally, "He's trainin' to be the next don, but fer now he mostly just does da boss's grunt work."
> ask Sally about Papa

> ask Sally about Papa
"Papa Macaroni's been so down lately," says Skunkface Sally. "I tried to cheer him up by jumping outta a giant canoli, but he ain't much interested in my sort."

"He ain't much interested in any sort right now," interjects Jimmy the Weasel. "Da boss been pinin' fer some good old-fashioned Italian spaghetti fer weeks, an' he can't keep his mind on da rackets. Da business is startin' ta suffer, capische?"
> ask Sally about moll

> ask Sally about moll
"I don't know what da boss sees in him," says Skunkface Sally, "What's he gone that I don't got?"

"I can think of one thing," says Jimmy the Weasel.

"You can hush your mouth, Jimmy the Weasel, nobody asked you fer no sass!"
> ask Sally about Jocko

> ask Sally about Jocko
"That ferret's only ever lost one fight, the Queen Molly grudge match. But I hear that was only cuz someone in the audience was jingling the change in their pocket and Jocko got distracted. That ferret loves jingle noises, I guess."
> ask Sally about Vinnie

> ask Sally about Vinnie
"That guy never gets out of the armory. But, if you need a gun, he's the guy to see."
> sit on stool

> sit on stool
"That's the spirit!" gushes Skunkface Sally as you scramble up onto the stool. "C'mon, Mulligan, deal her in!"

Two-Eyed Mulligan tosses a few playing cards in front of you as Skunkface Sally chatters away, explaining the rules of the game. "We're playing Tennessee Two-Step, jokers wild. The point of the game is you gotta get five of a kind, see?"

You pick up the cards, but they're all covered with random arcane sigils that mean nothing to you.

This game makes no sense to you, and you have a sneaking suspicion that, were he here, Percy would be counseling you very strongly not to get involved.  At least, not until you had some way to guarantee that you would win.

"Eh, this game's jest a buncha applesauce! Count me out, ya crumbums!" you sneer, throwing the confusing cards back across the table at Two-Eyed Mulligan.

"Aw, kid, c'mon! It's fun!" says Skunkface Sally, but you've already scrambled down off the stool. Percy would be proud!
