You are in a poker room.
You can see Skunk-Faced Sally, Two-Eyed Mulligan, a key, a stool and Jimmy the weasel.
You can go south.
A small, smoke-filled room.  A group of three scoundrels are gathered around a folding card table, each with his or her face buried into a hand of poker cards, muttering bets, chewing cigars, and occasionally tossing coins into a pile at the center of the table. You nearly choke on the thick tobacco fumes in the air.

There's a pile of cash, coins, and assorted knick-knacks at the center of the table; evidently the winner in their poker game gets to claim it all. You notice a large rusty key on top of the pile.
> sit on stool

> sit on stool

"Deal me in! Now I'm ready to play!" you cry, hopping onto the stool.  The other players squeal in delight, evidently delighted that such an obvious pigeon has joined the game, but their delight quickly turns to shock when you slam five identical printed pictures of Footloose Fritzi in flagrante delicto down on the table.

"Five of a kind! I wins!" you crow, grabbing the key from the pile in the middle of the room.

"Heeey! That's cheatin'!" cries Skunkface Sally, but you hush her with a quick finger to her lips.

"Ya jest said I needed FIVE of a kind ta win, crumbum! Ya didn't say it had to be five of a kind of yer cards, ya mook!"

"I...I guess so," muttered Skunkface Sally darkly. "What a ruse! I can't believe we've been rumbled by a kid!  Mulligan, get that twerp outta here!"

You feel a pair of rough hands lift you out of your seat and Two-Eyed Mulligan carries you, kicking and punching, to the door of the room and throws you out. You hear the door slam behind you, but it doesn't matter. At least you got the key!

