"Oy, Percy, can you read this malarkey?"

"Sure, Rags, let me take a look." He squints at the menu.  "Menu d' Ristaurante 'd Baleful Backwash. Specials: Mashed pigeon brains in a peach cling reduction.  Slightly bruised liver choplets with pomegranate leavings. Intestines stuffed with quinoa, peppers, and hard-boiled eggs."

"A quality selection!" says Percy, nodding in approval. "This must be a very high-end restaurant!"

"Bleh! It sounds like a bunch a' fancy pants hogwash ta me!" you say, "Gimmie a nice simple shoe and a frosty glass a' garbage juice any day!"
> give record to Percy

> give record to Percy
"Oy, Percy, can you read this? Wot's it say?" you ask, handing the record to Percy. Reading is too fancy for your blood, of course, but sometimes it pays to have a literate friend.

Percy squints at the label. "Jingoist's Delight: Five Heel-Clicking Military Marches to Angry up the Blood! 1. Kitcheners' Boys 2. America, Here's My Boy 3. Hock the Kaiser! 4. The Trenchfoot Shuffle 5. Bayonet to the Gut."
> ask Percy about pigeon

> ask Percy about pigeon
"Percy! There's a pigeon upstairs! How do I get rid of it?"

Percy goes pale. "A pigeon? Oh those are bad news! I shudder to think of all the good friends I've lost to a pigeon's unholy appetite! Rags, you know it's way too dangerous to get near one of those fiends, promise me that you'll keep your distance!"

"Er... how'm I s'posed ta rid o' it then?"

"I don't know, Rags, maybe find some sort of projectile?"
> ask Percy about terrier

> ask Percy about terrier
"Oy, Percy, ya know anything 'bout pigeon terriers?"

Percy snorts. "Normally I don't care for dogs, but pigeon terriers are an exception. I certainly applaud any dog that helps to reduce the surplus pigeon population. Awful monsters, those pigeons! And they call them 'flying rats.' What an insult!"

"So pigeon terriers, like, hunt pigeons?"

"Heavens no! They're useless for hunting. They're mostly good for chewing them up once they're dead. But at least that helps prevent the spread of pigeon carcass-borne disease."
