A small bare room, the walls are stained brick, the floor is worn concrete, lit by a dangling incandescent light bulb. Doors are set into the north, east, and west walls. Tony Macaroni leans against the wall next to the door to the east, glaring at you with disdain.

An aperture in the wall to the south leads to another room; you can hear excited whoops and shouts from within.
