You are in an office.
You can see Papa Macaroni, goons and a Lord Wartington statue.
You can go west.
A dimmly lit but spacious room that clearly belongs to a man of taste and refinement. The walls are lines with sturdy bookshelves of quality black walnut and ornate portraits, the floor covered with plush green wall-to-wall carpet, and a luxurious bearskin rug lies at the foot of the majestic oak desk that dominates the room.   A roaring fire in the hearth casts ominous shadows over the faces of the gangsters assembled here.

Behind the desk sits a short squat old man in a pinstriped suit, surrounded by some half dozen surly mafia goons, cigars clamped between gold teeth, fedoras cocked at menacing angles, faces criss-crossed by various interesting and disturbing scars.

> use shave on statue

> use shave on statue

You pull out the burma shave can, squeeze the nozzle, and quickly cover Lord Wartington in thick, foaming heaps of official Burma Shave brand shaving cream.

Moments later, the gangster's moll returns. He stops dead in his tracks as he sees Lord Wartington covered in foam.  "Oh no! Lord Wartington!" he cries, flinging himself at the base of the statue with an anguished cry. "What happened?! Who could have perpetuated such a villainous crime! This is the worst attack on the honor of Tappa Kegga Bru since those bullies at Sigma Figma Bi locked us all in that phonebooth..."

"I seen it all!" you pipe up, "It was a whole gang of, um, Sigma Figma Bi palookas! They ran in here and done desecrated yer pig! Why, if'n I had a gun right now, I'd show 'em a thing or two!"

The moll stands up, wipes his face on his sleeve, and stamps his foot angrily. "They shalln't get away with this travesty!" He fishes into his pocket and pulls out a scrap of paper, which he hands to you. "You seen like a strapping lass who loves a good scrape. I'm officially deputizing you to exact vengence for this slight! Go requisition yourself a gun and become mine wrath incarnate on those Sigma Figma Bi bullies!"
