You are in an armory.
You can see Skinny Vinnie Scaramuche.
You can go northwest.
A room dedicated to housing all the firepower that the mob uses in its constant turf wars against rival gangs, coppers, and G-men.  Behind the counter, you can see rows of pistols, knives, brass knuckles, and those tiny little clubs that gangster use for knocking people out.

The room is guarded by a reedy-looking man with a crooked nose, wearing the requisite pin-striped suit and a fedora.
> give note to Vinnie

> give note to Vinnie
"Hey crumbum, I gots a note! Now gimmie a gun!" you shout, waving the requisition note in Vinnie's face.

He takes the note and squints at it. "Yup, looks like they want you to rub out president of Sigma Figma Bi. So I gotta give you a Chicago Typewriter, loaded with one bullet."

"Wot? Just one bullet?" you say, disappointed, as Vinnie slides the inventory over the counter to you.

"Yeah, dese things ain't cheap ya know. Besides, ya don't need more than one now, do ya?"
