You are in an alley.
You can see a trashcan, a pigeon and a nest.
You can go southwest.
You're in a narrow, cramped alleyway between two old brown brick tenement buildings. The ground is littered with paper and garbage, and tin garbage cans are lined up against the sides of the passageway. You don't dare explore further than the vicinity right behind the trash cans for fear that the pigeon will see you.
> shoot pigeon

> shoot pigeon
Lucky for you, all those years of sling-shot practice really do port over to mansmanship! Crouching behind the trashcans, you pull out the chicago typewriter and line up the shot. BANG!! The single bullet goes flying and you tumble backward from the recoil.  But the bullet finds its mark and that awful pigeon tumbles to the ground with a single ear-splitting SQUAWK.
