You are in a kennel.
You can see Percy and a cage.
You can go east.
This room is filled with stacks of wire cages, most of which contain the trained greyhounds and miniature ponies that the mafia uses in fixing races down at the track.
> use file on cage

> use file on cage
"Oy, Percy! Look wot I got!" you crow, holding up the golden file for Percy to see.

His eyes go wide. "By the whiskers of Pious Norvegicus the rat pope!" he cries, "Rags, you've done it!"

"'Course I done it!" you say, attacking the cage bars with gusto. "I ain't 'bout ta let my best pal get et by no rotten ferret!"

After a few minutes of laborious grinding, the file breaks through the flimsy metal bars of the cage and the door swings open, allowing Percy to scurry out to freedom.

You grab him and place him carefully on your shoulder. "Alright, Percy, now you is free! And we can gets outta here!"

"We're not out of the woods yet, Rags!" says Percy. "We still have to get out of here without getting caught!"
